Craig,  I think you think I said the MILNET user should mail
to "user@Stanford.EDU" - I meant to suggest that the person should
mail to  "user%workstation@Stanford.EDU" to avoid just the problem
you suggest.  So  Stanford.EDU  should have to know about the workstation,
NOT about the user (though Berkeley appears to prefer the latter...).
I guess I wasn't clear on this.

It isn't that much effort to make workstations make their outgoing
address be "user%workstation@nic-known-host".  But add to this
the considerations of the mail load this places on the nic-known-host,
and the fact that all these workstations will have to be changed at
some time in the future when we decide they don't have to do this
anymore.

Peter
